cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with learning-to-rank methods for search engines. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new framework for Empirical Risk Minimization. Additionally, it could be classified under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with click models and natural language processing. Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are less likely but still possible sub-categories as the paper discusses biases in human-interactive systems and their impact on data analysis.
